ok so i have a few things to iron out before we begin the implementation. 
1. right now, person 1 is working on the ui whilst i am working on the algorithm. how do i ensure that person 1 and I don't create any conflicts when we pool our code together. to do this, we would have to a. be working in different files and have some sort of structure we agree upon and b. know exactly what data and how im pushing it so it can be pulled by the ui in the same way. am i correct in understanding this? 
2. after person 1 and I make our changes and write our code, how do we see if it's working or not inside of geoTab. we would need to have some sort of way to test this before we push our code to main. right now, there is this config file that we have imported inside geoTab that imports our code as an add-in. you can maybe refer to the geotab-vibe-coding-resources for the exact explanation on this. this is the config code:
{
    "name": "SmartRoute",
    "supportEmail": "https://github.com/avkap007/geotab-hackathon-smartroute",
    "version": "1.0",
    "items": [
        {
            "url": "https://avkap007.github.io/geotab-hackathon-smartroute/addin/smartroute.html",
            "path": "ActivityLink",
            "menuName": {
                "en": "SmartRoute"
            }
        }
    ],
    "isSigned": false
}

